articles.title: Gold price hits two-week high on weaker US jobs data ahead of NFP - FXStreet
articles.description: Gold hit a two-week high of $2,378 on Thursday after the US Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS) announced weaker-than-expected jobs data that kept US Treasury bond yields virtually unchanged, a tailwind for the golden metal.
